00:57:49.670 --> 00:57:54.390
Maybe let me say the following--
so by now we are convinced.

00:57:54.390 --> 00:57:57.090
Entangled states are great,
and we want to create them.

00:57:57.090 --> 00:58:02.670
And for photons, I showed you
that some simple element--

00:58:02.670 --> 00:58:08.660
beam splitters, Kerr medium--
can create entanglement.

00:58:08.660 --> 00:58:12.390
It's much harder to
do that with atoms.

00:58:12.390 --> 00:58:15.140
Now, we want to
do it with atoms,

00:58:15.140 --> 00:58:17.950
because atoms-- in
contrast to light-- they're

00:58:17.950 --> 00:58:20.730
pretty much staying still,
whereas photons always

00:58:20.730 --> 00:58:22.610
move at the speed of light.

00:58:22.610 --> 00:58:25.690
And the only way to
make photons stand still

00:58:25.690 --> 00:58:27.650
is you put them in a
cavity and then they

00:58:27.650 --> 00:58:28.860
bounce back and forth.

00:58:28.860 --> 00:58:31.940
But even in super cavities
with the highest reflectivity

00:58:31.940 --> 00:58:35.160
mirror, you get-- what are
the longest ring-down times

00:58:35.160 --> 00:58:37.970
you get-- fraction of
a second, milliseconds,

00:58:37.970 --> 00:58:39.570
depending kind of
in which domain

00:58:39.570 --> 00:58:42.010
you work-- microwave
domain, optical domain.

00:58:42.010 --> 00:58:45.960
Whereas atoms, you can hold onto
your qubits for a long time.

00:58:45.960 --> 00:58:50.460
So therefore, if you
want to use entanglement

00:58:50.460 --> 00:58:52.520
as a resource for
certain protocols,

00:58:52.520 --> 00:58:56.420
you want to have entangled atoms
where the entanglement would

00:58:56.420 --> 00:58:58.290
like for a long time.

00:58:58.290 --> 00:59:00.700
So the question
is now for atoms,

00:59:00.700 --> 00:59:03.610
we do not have perfect beam
splitters and perfect Kerr

00:59:03.610 --> 00:59:05.340
mediums.

00:59:05.340 --> 00:59:08.273
Also, we can control
interactions between atoms

00:59:08.273 --> 00:59:10.180
for [INAUDIBLE] using
VSEPR resonances,

00:59:10.180 --> 00:59:11.720
but that's another story.

00:59:11.720 --> 00:59:14.510
But now let me ask a question,
how do we entangle atoms?

00:59:30.630 --> 00:59:35.090
And I want to first
show you that if you

00:59:35.090 --> 00:59:40.100
had the right system,
things can be fairly simple.

00:59:40.100 --> 00:59:46.370
This is a suggestion which
was made almost 20 years ago,

00:59:46.370 --> 00:59:49.580
and it goes like
follows-- if you

00:59:49.580 --> 00:59:54.420
have a diatomic molecule
of two identical atoms,

00:59:54.420 --> 00:59:58.520
in this case
mercury, and mercury

00:59:58.520 --> 01:00:03.270
doesn't have-- this molecule
doesn't have any electron spin,

01:00:03.270 --> 01:00:06.730
but mercury has a nuclear spin.

01:00:06.730 --> 01:00:11.680
And if you now photo-dissociate
mercury and two mercury atoms

01:00:11.680 --> 01:00:17.070
fly away, then you have
separated a spin singlet

01:00:17.070 --> 01:00:18.860
into two parts.

01:00:18.860 --> 01:00:21.480
And now you have
created the Bell state

01:00:21.480 --> 01:00:22.840
up/down minus down/up.

01:00:25.880 --> 01:00:33.680
So you could say this is sort
of the example-- this realizes

01:00:33.680 --> 01:00:37.420
very closely the example I
gave you with the helium atom,

01:00:37.420 --> 01:00:40.210
where I said you have an
electron in spin up and spin

01:00:40.210 --> 01:00:44.220
down, but there was no way
to separate the electrons.

01:00:44.220 --> 01:00:47.730
Therefore, you can say it is a
state which has entanglement,

01:00:47.730 --> 01:00:50.970
but it's not entanglement
as a resource.

01:00:50.970 --> 01:00:54.620
But right now, here
it becomes a resource

01:00:54.620 --> 01:00:58.610
once you have found a
method to separate the two

01:00:58.610 --> 01:01:02.700
parts of the wave function that
you can give one to Alice, give

01:01:02.700 --> 01:01:07.570
one to Bob, and they can
perform the operations on it.

01:01:07.570 --> 01:01:09.470
Well, if it looks so
simple, why don't we

01:01:09.470 --> 01:01:12.810
have entangled atoms everywhere?

01:01:12.810 --> 01:01:15.650
This experiment has been
suggested 20 years ago,

01:01:15.650 --> 01:01:18.900
but nobody has done it,
or some several groups

01:01:18.900 --> 01:01:21.280
have worked on it.

01:01:21.280 --> 01:01:26.750
You need a molecule
with suitable states.

01:01:26.750 --> 01:01:30.660
You don't want any electron
spin which interferes with that.

01:01:30.660 --> 01:01:33.970
All you want to have
is two nuclear spins.

01:01:33.970 --> 01:01:35.650
You want a singlet state here.

01:01:35.650 --> 01:01:38.830
So those requirements
are not easily fulfilled

01:01:38.830 --> 01:01:41.760
with real atoms.

01:01:41.760 --> 01:01:45.400
Of course we liked-- and also
who wants to work with mercury?

01:01:45.400 --> 01:01:49.170
Mercury has transitions
in the ultraviolet.

01:01:49.170 --> 01:01:51.215
I think there's only one
group in the world who

01:01:51.215 --> 01:01:53.710
has operated a magneto
optic trap with mercury.

01:01:53.710 --> 01:01:56.440
So it's not your tabletop atom.

